[The repeated recommendation for horse owners is to vaccinate, vaccinate, vaccinate. Eastern equine encephalitis vaccine has been combined into a single vaccine with West Nile virus and, generally, for western equine encephalitis. This single vaccine is very protective for horses. Immunity to EEE decreases over time, and the vaccine is recommended to be given every 4 months to help protect horses.

Michigan can be found on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at: http://healthmap.org/r/2_1t.

Maryland may be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at: http://healthmap.org/r/2NNa. - Mod.TG]
